definitions.definition: A historical region and modern administrative region in the north of Belgium , consisting of the Dutch-speaking area of Belgium.
A historical county and cultural region of Western Europe , at its maximum covering most of Belgium , parts of northeast France , and a corner of the Netherlands ; in full, County of Flanders .
Two provinces in Belgian Flanders, West Flanders and East Flanders .
Ellipsis of French Flanders : a former province of France , now constituting the French department Nord .
The principal railway station in Lille , capital of the above.
An unincorporated community in Mount Olive , Morris County , New Jersey , United States .
